ive Image handles dynamic class loading. It seems like it only supports loading classes already in the image, which is a limitation. I could still test `setServiceClassLoader` to see if the classloader returns resources from memory. There's also the concern about dynamic service providers not being included unless referenced in the test. Additionally, there's a question about supporting enum/list in configuration. I might test the sampler property for its functionality and ensure it behaves as expected without duplication.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating trace sampler testing options**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to retest the trace sampler since it already utilizes the sampler customizer. There’s the \\\"parentbased_always_off\\\" setting, and I could use `public span.isRecording` to check if it’s false, but it might be less unique. I also want to test if the environment/system property auto-configuration distinguishes itself from existing properties. Changing global system properties could affect my tests, so I need to be cautious and possibly use a unique service name to avoid conflicts. I’ll keep an eye on how system properties are managed.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZJPGIVcoRR15ensfPxI9TG5O|fc_03a87861a5a60c340169f6576897fc819ca967d95f262f380d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "jar tf ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/io.opentelemetry/opentelemetry-sdk-extension-autoconfigure/1.25.0-alpha/*/opentelemetry-sdk-extension-autoconfigure-1.25.0-alpha.jar | sed 's#/#.#g' | rg 'io.opentelemetry.sdk.autoconfigure.*\\.class$' | head -80", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2016, "output": 1472, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23456, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777751892974, "responseId": "resp_03a87861a5a60c340169f6575584d8819ca989d7709d01af4